benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/cache/accounts/{accountId} - Invalidates Caches per account level

covered: Valid Request: Scenario @TC01 covers successful cache invalidation with a valid accountId.
Non-Existent Account: Scenario @TC02 tests invalid accountId (non-existent).
Invalid Format: Scenario @TC03 covers invalid accountId format.
Missing Path Parameter: Scenario @TC04 tests missing accountId in URL.
Unauthorized Access: Scenarios @TC05 and @TC06 cover missing or invalid authentication tokens.
System Under Load: Scenario @TC07 addresses degraded system performance.
Dependent Service Unavailable: Scenario @TC08 tests cache service downtime.
Extra Query Parameters: Scenario @TC09 covers additional query params.
Large AccountId: Scenario @TC10 tests maximum-length accountId.
Unsupported Methods: Scenario @TC11 tests method not allowed.
Regression for UUID pattern: Scenario @TC12 covers previous UUID validation issues.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets requiring pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for unauthorized users beyond missing/invalid tokens.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate high request volume or throttling.
Caching Headers: No scenarios verify presence or correctness of caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify handling of large datasets.
Include explicit authorization tests for different user roles and missing credentials.
Implement rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure system stability under load.
Verify caching headers in responses to ensure proper cache control and validation.
